  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6761.5 sitting above the max negative gamma strike at 6750 (-61.3B), dealers are currently forced to buy the rally as they hedge their short gamma positions, creating mechanical buying pressure that's amplifying the move higher. The massive negative GEX wall cluster between 6745-6765 (all exceeding -31B) means any pullback toward these levels will trigger aggressive dealer buying, while the positive gamma ceiling at 6800 (+27.6B) represents the key resistance where dealers flip to selling pressure. The 30%+ GEX surge and wall break detection confirms we're in full breakout mode with dealers acting as momentum accelerators rather than stabilizers.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect continued volatile trending moves with strong buying support on any dips toward 6750 and selling resistance near 6800.",
